# Commands → Skills → Agents

When the user types a command, invoke the matching skill.

| Command | Skill | Agent | Model |
|---------|-------|-------|-------|
| `/spec [name]` | `spec-create` | Planner | **opus 4.6** (DAG reasoning) |
| `/split <ID>` | `spec-split` | Splitter | composer-2 fast |
| `/run [ID]` | `spec-run` | Executor | composer-2 fast |
| `/review [ID]` | `spec-review` | Reviewer | composer-2 fast |
| `/status` | `dag-status` | Orchestrator | composer-2 fast |
| `/next` | `dag-next` | Orchestrator | composer-2 fast |

## Routing Rules

- `/spec` is the ONLY command that triggers opus — it designs the DAG
- All other commands use composer-2 fast
- `/next` chains skills automatically (status → run/split/review)
- `/run` without ID = run ALL ready specs in parallel

## Implicit Triggers

Skills also activate on natural language:
- "create a spec" / "plan" / "new task" → `spec-create`
- "break this down" / "too big" → `spec-split`
- "build" / "implement" / "execute" → `spec-run`
- "check" / "validate" → `spec-review`
- "progress" / "where are we" → `dag-status`
- "continue" / "keep going" / "what's next" → `dag-next`
